Author: j4jackj
Text: you can't have gained fat or muscle, but you can have gained weight. water weight, which your body needs to make an effort to repair itself.

Author: intertropical
Text: You definitely can’t have gained any “real” weight/fat. That may or may not reflect on the scale, because of shit like water retention – working out can contribute to this! But no matter what’s on the scale itself it’s impossible to gain “actual” weight on such a deficit. Sending love <3
